kernel-xanmod: kernel-xanmod (Desktop focused 64-bit Xanmod Linux kernel)
kernel-xanmod:
kernel-xanmod: This is a xanmod Linux kernel with modified or generic config file
kernel-xanmod: and built-in support for most disk controllers. To use filesystems,
kernel-xanmod: or to load support for a SCSI or other controller, then you'll
kernel-xanmod: need to load one or more kernel modules using an initial ramdisk,
kernel-xanmod: or initrd. For more information about creating an initrd, see the
kernel-xanmod: README.initrd file in the /boot directory.
kernel-xanmod:
kernel-xanmod: SMP is "Symmetric multiprocessing", or multiple CPU/core support.
